track_notes:
This was the route I took to ascend to the summit. I took a different route off the summit and eventually down to rejoin the ascent route at Stronmagachan farm, but it was fairly severe so would suggest you utilise the ascent route for your descent route. 

Park on the A819 beside the BT Telephone building and head back to the access road to the farm. On a approaching the farm a hill road spurs off to your left.  Follow this road upwards but it peters out fairly quickly.

Once on the summit great views down to Arran, Jura and the inner Hedrides also Cruchan GM/WS-013 and its hydro dam and the back-end of the Arrochar Alps

Enjoy Jack GM4COX
